news.title: Dawat-e-Hadiyah buys 'Killick House' in South Mumbai for over Rs 72 crore
news.para: The trust has bought the leasehold and ownership rights of the building on Hornby Road from Nippon Investment and Finance Company that was previously part of the Videocon Group and functioned as a promoter group entity for Videocon Industries.

news.title: Nagpur civic body sells 1.25 lakh sq ft plot for Rs 235 crore
news.para: The plot is set to be developed into a premium commercial complex. The deal not only sets a new benchmark for Nagpur's real estate market but also highlights the growing commercial appeal of Orange City Street corridor.

news.title: Bengaluru development body increases tax on its properties by 20% to 45%
news.para: Over 1.2 lakh property owners protest poor roads, irregular water supply, and power issues that continue to plague several BDA layouts across the city

news.title: Maharashtra approves ownership transfer of 28 PMC, PCMC land parcels to Maha Metro
news.para: This move will grant Maharashtra Metro Rail Corporation Limited (Maha Metro) full ownership of the plots, enabling them to commercially develop the properties and boost non-fare box revenue.

news.title: Delhi: DDA razes illegal farmhouses on encroached land in Sainik Farms
news.para: According to officials, the illegal structures had been under development for a long time and were part of a broader trend of unauthorised land use in the area.

news.title: NGT issues notice to TDI City over non-functional STPs, water pollution
news.para: ​​This action follows findings submitted by a joint committee formed by the NGT to investigate complaints about untreated wastewater and water stagnation in the area.

news.title: YEIDA to launch portal for over 4,500 homebuyers of Jaiprakash Associates
news.para: A subcommittee of various homebuyers' associations has been set up to represent collective interests and coordinate with YEIDA.

news.title: E-draw for 708 affordable flats will be held again in Gurugram
news.para: ​The decision to scrap the e-draw — announced through a public notice on Thursday (May 1) — came after alleged "technical discrepancies and regional bias" raised serious concerns over the fairness of the process.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Builder digs for basement & damages drain, society flooded
news.para: In Prateek Grand City, residents of the upper floors claimed they were "trapped" in their homes as the maintenance team was forced to shut lifts as putrid water filled the subbasement. The society's 24 towers, each with 28 floors, have nearly 3,000 residents.

news.title: Over 180 housing societies in Pimpri Chinchwad issued notices for non-functional STPs
news.para: A senior civic official said at least 50 of the said societies were served a third and final notice, which warned that the civic body would cut water supply if the STPs are not made functional immediately.

news.title: Carlyle Group exits PNB Housing Finance; sells 10.44% stake for Rs 2,712 crore
news.para: ​US-based Carlyle group, through its affiliate Quality Investment Holdings PCC, sold more than 2.71 crore shares, or 10.44 per cent stake, in PNB Housing Finance on the National Stock Exchange (NSE) and the BSE.

news.title: Prime minister launches projects worth Rs 58,000 crore in Andhra Pradesh
news.para: The establishment of Amaravati as a capital city is touted to be Naidu's dream project, following the bifurcation of the state in 2014 when Hyderabad, capital of the then united AP, became the capital for the newly carved Telangana.

news.title: Sebi proposes ease of doing business measures for REITs, InvITs
news.para: Under the present rule, REITs and InvITs are required to get their assets valued regularly and submit these valuation reports to stock exchanges and unitholders.

news.title: Mumbai: MHADA to make 15 crore official documents public
news.para: "By making 15 crore official documents available to citizens, we are reducing the dependency on Right to Information (RTI) applications and making access to information straightforward and hassle-free," Jaiswal said.

news.title: Mumbai: MHADA receives ₹11,334.51 crore in actual receipts in FY25
news.para: In FY25, ₹5,000 crore was received under revenue receipts which includes income from Floor Space Index (FSI) premiums, interest on investments, building permit fees, rent, and service charges.

news.title: Sunteck Realty's net profit declines 50.28% in Q4 FY25
news.para: Sunteck Realty's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 217.83 crore in Q4 FY25, a drop of 49.92 per cent from Rs 434.99 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Goa police register case over illegal sand mining at Xelvona
news.para: The case was filed based on a formal complaint by Nathan Afonso, the mamlatdar of Quepem taluka and the flying squad in charge.

news.title: Construction spending in US falls 0.5% in March 2025
news.para: Spending on private construction projects fell 0.6%. Investment in residential construction slipped 0.4%, with outlays on new single-family projects edging up 0.1%.

news.title: Builders FirstSource cuts annual revenue forecast for 2025
news.para: Elevated mortgage rates and tariff-driven macroeconomic uncertainty have prompted potential customers to reconsider buying homes, leading to suppressed demand for new houses.
